<h2 class="display-4">about</h2>

<h2>why zeromev</h2>

<p class="lead">Zeromev aims to protect Ethereum users from frontrunning, censorship and other harmful transaction reordering attacks.</p>
<p>Figures show that billions of dollars have been lost by users to such exploits, often called Miner Extractable Value (MEV).</p>

<h2>zeromev aims</h2>

<p>Funded by a grant from the Ethereum Foundation, we aim to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Empower Users by providing information to help users understand and avoid MEV</li>
<li>Protect Users by researching and advocating for genuinely preventative protocol level solutions</li>
</ul>

<h2>what’s the problem?</h2>
<p>The Ethereum blockchain is written by consensus, but the content of each block is chosen by just one miner acting as a centralized intermediary between you and the blockchain.</p>
<p>Miners can profit from users by frontrunning, backrunning, sandwiching and generally exploiting transactions in their block however they choose.</p>

